title: Show HN: On-demand, 100% AI-generated holiday cards (free e-card option)
text:
Hi HN, I'm working on generative AI and hypercustomization - I hope greetings cards will be the first of a huge range of on-demand products we can enable consumers to tailor to their exact tastes using AI!

This site lets you choose one of over 40 holiday card themes, generate image ideas and messages with GPT-3, and then create your own images one of 25 art styles. No prompt engineering needed!

You can mail or order cards on-demand, or send an e-card for free.

Happy holidays, please let me know what you think! Francis

Ask HN: Who is using Crossplane today in their infrastructure?
text: We have had incidents where I work of developers or folks new with terraform on the team making manual changes to resources they should not have made, resulting in downtime. I did my own little PoC at https://github.com/autotune/bank-of-anthos/tree/main/aws that implements Crossplane on an EKS cluster, which then builds out its own EKS cluster and resources to support that, and installs a demo provided by Google via helm. What are the cons of this setup? So far I have identified the lack of ability to do a terraform plan beforehand and and the fact that Crossplane is basically brand new on the scene as possible set backs, but the features it offers in exchange for that just seem incredible. What are your experiences or thoughts on it?
